# Keep Cursor's file/retrieval indexer out of build output and binary assets.
#
# Why this file exists: `target/` reached 56 GB during a multi-agent session (repeated
# `--features net` / `--no-default-features` flips each produce their own artifacts). Nothing was
# telling the indexer to skip it. This is about the INDEXER, not rust-analyzer — rust-analyzer works
# off `cargo metadata` and dependency sources in `~/.cargo/registry`, and only reaches into `target/`
# for proc-macro dylibs and build-script output. If rust-analyzer is the memory problem, the levers
# are its own settings (pin `cargo.features`, drop `--all-targets` from its check command, disable
# cache priming), not this file.

# Build output.
/target
/dist
/build

# Binary assets: the source of truth is the .blend / .glb, and neither is useful to index as text.
*.blend
*.blend1
*.glb
*.gltf
*.png
*.jpg

# Research/scrape cache.
.firecrawl/

# Trace captures: `SPIKE_TRACE` / `SUSP_TRACE` write JSONL at 64 Hz, so these get large fast and
# carry no reusable meaning outside `scripts/jitter/`.
*.jsonl
*.log

.DS_Store
